      "writtenOn": "2011-06-01T11:45:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The method exchangeIccAPDU returns the response APDU from the UICC. On any communication error, the response APDU is \"6f 00\" (see EVENT_EXCHANGE_APDU_DONE). So, in any case, the method exchangeIccAPDU returns a valid response APDU (\u003d string with at least two characters). Again, the method transmitIccLogicalChannel does not parse the response APDU. The caller parses the response APDU.",
