      "writtenOn": "2011-06-01T11:45:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The method openIccLogicalChannel returns an unsigned 32-bit session key (as defined in 3GPP TS 27.007). The modem returns a session key instead of the channel number for security reasons (you have to know to the session key to use the logical channel). The value zero is an invalid session key, and therefore is used to indicate an error. Currently the caller (UiccTerminal.java) translates the session key to a channel number and back, but we could move this functionality to RIL. Then, the method openIccLogicalChannel would return a channel number (in the range 1 to 20), or an error code (-1 to -x). Since 3GPP TS 27.007 covers AT commands based modems only, and other types of modems might have a different interface, this solution looks better than the current one. Any comments?",
      "parentUuid": "AAABBn///NE\u003d",
      "revId": "40931b3703a9e526c29b6620b1a94b540cdcf045",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
